<FONT face=arial><P align=center>
<b>How do I add formatting and photos to my News Story?</b><br><BR>
</p>
<P align=left>

Your news story is rendered HTML on the "News" page, so you can write the whole thing in HTML and expect it to come out on the other side.

On the assumption that most people don't know any HTML here's how to do some useful stuff:<br><BR>

<li> Make some words <b>Bold</b>:<br>
Surround your bit of text in &lt;b>   &lt;/b><br><BR>

<li> Make some words <i>Italic</i>:<br>
Surround your bit of text in &lt;i>   &lt;/i><BR><BR>

<li> Make some words <u>Underlined</u>:<br>
Surround your bit of text in &lt;u>   &lt;/u><br><br><li> 

Carriage Return:<br>Add &lt;br&gt; where you want the break. 
<br>
<br>

<li> Add a picture:<br>
A touch more complicated, but basically just add this piece of code to the article:<br><br>
&lt;img src="www.location_of_your_image.com/name_of_the_image.jpg"><br><BR>

and replace the url with the link to the photo. <BR><BR>

The photo <b>must</b> be hosted somewhere on the WWW.





